  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IDH Pulp and paper program</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Sustainable Trade Initiative for Pulp and Paper (STIPP) aims to mainstream sustainability in the pulp and paper industry in Indonesia and China. With its initial focus on Indonesia, IDH supports the industry with a learning and innovations platform working to find solutions that reduce deforestation and increase clean manufacturing. STIPP partners with producers to encourage sectorwide adoption of sustainable forest management, high carbon stock standard/guidance, best peatland management, social management practices, resource-efficient and waste-management practices, and integrated landscape-level sustainability management.</narrative>
  </description>
